## Domain Characterization

**CRITICAL**: Before creating any domain class (Entity, Value Object, Domain Event, etc.), you MUST read the [Domain Characterization Guide](../docs/domain-characterization.md).

This guide explains:

- **Entities**: When to use entities (identity + lifecycle)
- **Value Objects**: When to use value objects (immutable, no identity)
- **Domain Events**: When to use domain events (past events)
- **Aggregates**: How to organize entities into aggregates
- **Repositories**: One repository per aggregate root
- **Services**: Domain services vs Application services

**Key Principle**: Favor Value Objects over Entities when possible. Value Objects are simpler, immutable, and require less lifecycle management.

## Key Patterns & Concepts

1. **CQRS Pattern**:
   - Commands (CreateRoleCommand) and Queries (GetRolesQuery) are separated
   - @nestjs/cqrs is used for command/query dispatching

```typescript
// src/application/authorization/commands/create-role/create-role.command.ts
export class CreateRoleCommand implements ICommand {
  constructor(public readonly payload: CreateRoleDto) {}
}

// src/application/authorization/commands/create-role/create-role.handler.ts
@CommandHandler(CreateRoleCommand)
export class CreateRoleHandler implements ICommandHandler<CreateRoleCommand> {
  constructor(
    @Inject(ROLE_REPOSITORY_PORT)
    private readonly roleRepository: RoleRepositoryPort,
  ) {}

  async execute(command: CreateRoleCommand): Promise<Role> {
    const { payload } = command;

    // Check if role already exists
    const existingRole = await this.roleRepository.findByName(payload.name);
    if (existingRole) {
      throw new UnprocessableEntityException({
        status: HttpStatus.UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY,
        errors: { name: 'roleAlreadyExists' },
      });
    }

    // Create role entity
    const role = Role.create({
      name: payload.name,
      permissions: payload.permissions,
    });

    return await this.roleRepository.create(role);
  }
}
```

2. **Domain-Driven Design**:
   - Rich domain models with encapsulated business logic
   - **IMPORTANT**: Before creating domain classes, read [Domain Characterization Guide](../docs/domain-characterization.md) to understand when to use Entities, Value Objects, Domain Events, Aggregates, and Services
   - Value Objects for type safety:

```typescript
// src/domain/value-objects/email.ts
export class Email {
  private constructor(private readonly value: string) {
    this.validate(value);
  }

  static create(value: string): Email {
    return new Email(value);
  }

  private validate(value: string): void {
    const emailRegex = /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/;
    if (!emailRegex.test(value)) {
      throw new DomainException('Invalid email format');
    }
  }

  getValue(): string {
    return this.value;
  }

  equals(other: Email): boolean {
    return this.value === other.value;
  }
}

// src/domain/enums/auth-providers.enum.ts
export enum AuthProvidersEnum {
  EMAIL = 'email',
  GOOGLE = 'google',
  APPLE = 'apple',
  FACEBOOK = 'facebook',
}
